  "text": "These results suggest that it is likely that the GSTM1 deletion has fitness effects, but it is independent of the selective sweep we observed for the Tanuki haplogroup. To explain these observations, we hypothesize that Tanuki haplogroup affect the function of multiple genes in the GSTM gene family and not just GSTM1. Consequently, the putative adaptive phenotype is a result of combination of these effects. Such a perspective has precedent where other studies described likely adaptive haplotypes that have effects on multiple metabolism gene families, such as IRX [CITATION_1] and FAD (Fumagalli et al. 2015) .",
